Senior judges have identified three legal points of public importance for consideration, granting leave to appeal to the UK's highest court. The court has been asked to consider issues relating to the Northern Ireland Act and the Act of Union . Lady Chief Justice Dame Siobhan Keegan confirmed: “We have considered the papers, and in the circumstances of this case we are going to grant leave to appeal to the Supreme Court.” The Northern Ireland Protocol was implemented at the start of 2021 to prevent harsh border controls in Ireland. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...